title: Haystacks, midday
about:
This is one of eight paintings of wheat stacks that Monet
began in the late summer and autumn of 1890. The artist
continued to paint stacks of wheat in his neighbour's field through
the winter of 1890-91, producing seventeen more canvases of the
same subject. To this might be added further five paintings of
stacks made in the autumn and winter of 1888-89, bringing the
total number of Monet's wheat stack themed paintings to at least
thirty.

title: London Parliament
about:
Le Havre museum acquired London Parliament along with
two other Monet's paintings, Cliffs at Varengeville and Waterlilies,
in 1910. Purchased directly from the artist for the symbolic
amount of 3,000 francs, these paintings were added to the small 2
at the time municipal collection of impressionist works that is now
the second of France for the number of impressionist
paintings.

title: Houses of Parliament, Sunlight Effect
about:
The painting is one of Claude Monet's Houses of
Parliament series that contains 19 canvases all exactly the same
size and depicting the same scene from the same vantage point,
Monet's window at St Thomas' Hospital overlooking the Thames.
They are however painted at different times of the day and at
different weather circumstances.
